<h2>General Online Review Statistics</h2>
<p>These numbers show how deeply reviews influence the modern buyer journey.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Consumer review behavior statistics for 2026" src="/images/blog/online-review-consumer-behavior-stats.webp" /></p>
<p><strong>1. 95% of consumers read online reviews before making a purchase.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.podium.com/">Podium</a>, 2025)
Nearly every buyer checks reviews. The 5% who do not are statistical outliers.</p>
<p><strong>2. 84% of consumers use Google to find business reviews.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.brightlocal.com/research/local-consumer-review-survey-2025/">BrightLocal</a>, 2025)
Google is the default starting point. No other platform comes close for <a href="/blog/local-seo-statistics/">local search</a>.</p>
<p><strong>3. 74% of consumers check 2 or more review websites before deciding.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.brightlocal.com/research/local-consumer-review-survey-2025/">BrightLocal</a>, 2025)
A single platform presence is not enough. Buyers cross-reference.</p>
<p><strong>4. The average consumer reads 10 reviews before trusting a business.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.statista.com/">Statista</a>, 2025)
Businesses with fewer than 10 reviews face an immediate credibility gap.</p>
<p><strong>5. 42% of consumers trust online reviews as much as personal recommendations.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.brightlocal.com/research/local-consumer-review-survey-2025/">BrightLocal</a>, 2025)
This number dropped from 79% in 2020. Consumers are more skeptical now, but reviews still rank second only to word-of-mouth.</p>
<p><strong>6. 46% of consumers are suspicious of reviews that appear AI-written.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.brightlocal.com/research/local-consumer-review-survey-2025/">BrightLocal</a>, 2025)
AI-generated reviews erode trust. Authentic language matters more than ever.</p>
<p><strong>7. 48% of consumers read AI-generated review summaries but still check individual reviews.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.brightlocal.com/research/local-consumer-review-survey-2025/">BrightLocal</a>, 2025)
AI summaries are a starting point, not a replacement. Buyers still want the raw data.</p>
<p><strong>8. Only 4% of consumers never read online business reviews.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.brightlocal.com/research/local-consumer-review-survey-2025/">BrightLocal</a>, 2025)
Reviews are no longer optional. They are part of the purchase decision for 96% of adults.</p>
<h2>Review Platform Market Share Statistics</h2>
<p>Not all review platforms carry equal weight. Google dominates, but niche platforms still matter for specific industries.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Review platform market share showing Google at 73%" src="/images/blog/review-platform-market-share.webp" /></p>
<p><strong>9. Google holds 73% of all online reviews.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.reviewtrackers.com/">ReviewTrackers</a>, 2025)
Nearly 3 out of 4 reviews live on Google. Optimizing your <a href="/blog/optimize-google-business-profile/">Google Business Profile</a> is the highest-priority action.</p>
<p><strong>10. Yelp holds 6% of online review volume.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.reviewtrackers.com/">ReviewTrackers</a>, 2025)
Yelp remains important for restaurants, home services, and healthcare. But its overall share continues to shrink.</p>
<p><strong>11. TripAdvisor and Facebook each hold 3% of review volume.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.reviewtrackers.com/">ReviewTrackers</a>, 2025)
TripAdvisor matters for hospitality. Facebook reviews are declining in perceived reliability.</p>
<p><strong>12. 93% of Facebook users distrust reviews on that platform.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.brightlocal.com/research/local-consumer-review-survey-2025/">BrightLocal</a>, 2025)
Facebook reviews carry the lowest trust score of any major platform.</p>
<p><strong>13. Yelp receives 26,830 new reviews per minute.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/online-review-statistics/">DemandSage</a>, 2025)
Despite its shrinking market share, Yelp still generates massive volume. For a deeper look at the dominant platform, see our <a href="/blog/google-reviews-statistics/">Google reviews statistics</a> breakdown.</p>
<p><strong>14. 48% of U.S. adults turn to local news outlets for business reviews.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.brightlocal.com/research/local-consumer-review-survey-2025/">BrightLocal</a>, 2025)
Local news and community sites are an underused review channel for <a href="/blog/local-seo-guide/">local businesses</a>.</p>
