<h2>Review Impact on Purchasing Decisions</h2>
<p>Reviews do not just build trust. They directly move revenue.</p>
<p><strong>15. 93% of consumers say online reviews influence their purchase decisions.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.podium.com/">Podium</a>, 2025)
Reviews are the second most influential factor after price for most buyers.</p>
<p><strong>16. Products with 5+ reviews have a 270% higher purchase likelihood.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://spiegel.medill.northwestern.edu/">Spiegel Research Center</a>, Northwestern University)
The threshold is low. Five reviews change buying behavior dramatically.</p>
<p><strong>17. Displaying reviews boosts sales by 19.8% on average.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://spiegel.medill.northwestern.edu/">Spiegel Research Center</a>, Northwestern University)
This applies across categories. The lift is higher for expensive products (380%) than low-cost ones (190%).</p>
<p><strong>18. 44% of shoppers will not purchase from a business with zero reviews.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/online-review-statistics/">DemandSage</a>, 2025)
No reviews is worse than a few mediocre reviews. Silence signals risk.</p>
<p><strong>19. 86% of shoppers hesitate to buy from businesses with negative reviews.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://wiserreview.com/blog/online-review-statistics/">WiserReview</a>, 2026)
Hesitation does not mean refusal. But unchecked negative reviews create measurable friction. Learn how to <a href="/blog/respond-to-negative-google-reviews/">respond to negative reviews</a> effectively.</p>
<p><strong>20. 58% of consumers will pay more or travel farther for businesses with positive reviews.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.podium.com/">Podium</a>, 2025)
Reviews override convenience and price for a majority of buyers.</p>
<p><strong>21. 72% of travelers say online reviews influence their booking decisions.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://wiserreview.com/blog/online-review-statistics/">WiserReview</a>, 2026)
For hospitality and tourism businesses, reviews are the primary conversion driver.</p>
<h2>Star Rating and Review Volume Statistics</h2>
<p>The specific number of stars and the total count of reviews both affect how consumers evaluate a business.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Star ratings and revenue impact data" src="/images/blog/review-star-rating-revenue-impact.webp" /></p>
<p><strong>22. 57% of consumers require a business to have 4+ stars before they will use it.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.brightlocal.com/research/local-consumer-review-survey-2025/">BrightLocal</a>, 2025)
Anything below 4 stars filters out more than half of potential customers.</p>
<p><strong>23. 31% of consumers now require 4.5+ stars.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://wiserreview.com/blog/online-review-statistics/">WiserReview</a>, 2026)
This threshold nearly doubled from 17% in the prior year. Expectations are rising fast.</p>
<p><strong>24. A 1-star improvement in rating increases revenue by 5-9%.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://spiegel.medill.northwestern.edu/">Spiegel Research Center</a>, Northwestern University)
Moving from 3.5 to 4.5 stars can mean a 10-18% revenue gain.</p>
<p><strong>25. 67% of consumers will not trust high ratings without substantial review volume.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/online-review-statistics/">DemandSage</a>, 2025)
A 5.0 rating with 3 reviews is less convincing than a 4.6 with 200 reviews.</p>
<p><strong>26. 43% of consumers prefer businesses with more than 100 reviews.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/online-review-statistics/">DemandSage</a>, 2025)
Volume signals legitimacy. Businesses should consistently <a href="/blog/ask-customers-for-reviews/">ask customers for reviews</a> to build this number.</p>
<p><strong>27. Products with 11-30 reviews convert 68% higher than those with zero.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://spiegel.medill.northwestern.edu/">Spiegel Research Center</a>, Northwestern University)
The sweet spot is 26-50 reviews for most products and services.</p>
