<h2>Review Response Statistics</h2>
<p>How businesses handle reviews matters as much as the reviews themselves.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Review response statistics for 2026" src="/images/blog/review-response-statistics-2026.webp" /></p>
<p><strong>28. 73% of customer reviews received a business response in 2024.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://birdeye.com/blog/state-of-online-reviews/">Birdeye</a>, 2025)
This is up from 63% the prior year. More businesses recognize responses matter.</p>
<p><strong>29. 75% of businesses never address negative reviews.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/online-review-statistics/">DemandSage</a>, 2025)
Three out of 4 businesses ignore their most damaging reviews. Use these <a href="/blog/review-response-templates/">review response templates</a> to fix that gap.</p>
<p><strong>30. Businesses that respond to 25%+ of reviews earn 35% more revenue.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.keeping.com/">Keeping</a>, 2025)
Responding is not just good manners. It is a revenue driver.</p>
<p><strong>31. 63% of consumers expect a response within 2-3 days to 1 week.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.brightlocal.com/research/local-consumer-review-survey-2025/">BrightLocal</a>, 2025)
Speed matters. A response after 2 weeks reads as indifference.</p>
<p><strong>32. Manual review responses grew from 58% to 61% of all responses.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://birdeye.com/blog/review-response-trends-2025/">Birdeye</a>, 2025)
Businesses are shifting away from automated replies. Consumers notice the difference.</p>
<p><strong>33. Total review volume increased 13% year over year in 2024.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://birdeye.com/blog/state-of-online-reviews/">Birdeye</a>, 2025)
More reviews mean more data for consumers and more <a href="/blog/local-seo-ranking-factors/">local SEO ranking signals</a> for search engines.</p>
