<h2>Fake Review Statistics</h2>
<p>Fake reviews are a growing problem. Regulators and platforms are responding.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Fake review statistics for 2026" src="/images/blog/fake-review-statistics-2026.webp" /></p>
<p><strong>34. An estimated 30% of all online reviews are fake.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.invespcro.com/">Invesp</a>, 2025)
Nearly 1 in 3 reviews is fabricated. This erodes consumer trust across every platform.</p>
<p><strong>35. Google removed or blocked 240 million policy-violating reviews in 2024.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://blog.google/">Google</a>, 2025)
Google is actively fighting fake reviews at scale. But 240 million removals shows the scope of the problem.</p>
<p><strong>36. 82% of consumers have read a fake review in the past year.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.invespcro.com/">Invesp</a>, 2025)
Most consumers encounter fake reviews regularly. Learn how to <a href="/blog/handle-fake-google-reviews/">handle fake Google reviews</a> when they target your business.</p>
<p><strong>37. 67% of consumers consider fake reviews a major problem.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.agilitypr.com/">AgilityPR</a>, 2025)
Consumer awareness is high. Brands caught using fake reviews face permanent trust damage.</p>
<p><strong>38. An estimated 42% of Amazon reviews may be fake.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://wiserreview.com/blog/online-review-statistics/">WiserReview</a>, 2026)
Amazon has the highest estimated fake review rate of any major platform.</p>
<p><strong>39. The FTC can fine businesses up to $53,088 per fake review violation.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.ftc.gov/business-guidance/blog/2025/12/warning-letter-or-ten-businesses-comply-ftcs-consumer-review-rule">FTC</a>, 2025)
The FTC issued its first enforcement warnings under the Consumer Review Rule in December 2025. Penalties will rise with inflation adjustments.</p>
